 Given the equations, we can solve for $\displaystyle\frac{w}{x}$ by multiplying the given ratios: $\dfrac{x}{y} = (\dfrac{w}{x} \cdot \dfrac{x}{y}) \cdot (\dfrac{y}{z} \cdot \dfrac{z}{w}) \cdot (\dfrac{z}{w} \cdot \dfrac{w}{x})=(\dfrac{w}{x} \cdot \dfrac{x}{y}) \cdot (\dfrac{y}{z} \cdot \dfrac{z}{w}) \cdot (\dfrac{z}{w}) = \dfrac{w}{x}.$
Since we know the values of the ratios given, we have
\begin{align}
\frac{w}{z} &= \left(\frac{w}{x}\cdot\frac{x}{y}\cdot\frac{y}{z}\right)\\
&= \left(\frac{w}{x}\right)\cdot\frac{w}{z}\\
\frac{w}{z} &= \frac{w}{x}\frac{w}{z}\\
1 &= \frac{w}{x}\\
\frac{w}{z}&=1
\end{align}
